          "body": "The chapter's central verse is 6:10, and its central phrase is the comparative *as he had been doing previously*. Daniel does not pray more loudly to prove a point, nor more secretly to evade the law. He prays *the same*. Three features matter: (1) *toward Jerusalem* — fulfilling Solomon's prayer (1 Kings 8:48); his orientation is covenantal. (2) *three times a day on his knees* — the disciplined rhythm of Psalm 55:17, established long before the crisis. (3) *praying and giving thanks* — gratitude included even as the decree threatens his life. The lesson is precise: the prayer life that withstands persecution is the one already in place before persecution arrives. Crisis does not produce devotion; it reveals it."
